release.notes:
"He Who Has Not Been At Aragon Knows Not What A Paradise Is!"

Live Recording from July 2nd, 2003 at the Aragon Ballroom in Chicago.

℗ & © 2013 Third Man Records, LLC.
Manufactured at United Record Pressing in Nashville, TN

All songs (Peppermint Stripe Music, BMI) except:
A3: Special Rider Music, SESAC
D5: BMI
A6: APRS, BMI
B2 & B3: MPCA King Of Spades, SESAC
B2 (Traditional)
C6 [Party Of Special Things To Do]: Honeysuckle Music Company Inc. BMI


D1 starts off with 'This Protector' though not mentioned on cover or label of release.

Third Man Records Vault Package #16 also included this [url=http://www.discogs.com/White-Stripes-I-Want-To-Be-The-Boy-To-Warm-Your-Mothers-Heart-Little-Acorns/release/4701919]single[/url] and the 56 page book Pictures from Elephant by David Swanson.
